discovery_document.template:
Client Meeting Record & Fact-Find Template

1. Meeting & Client Data

Client Name(s): [Insert Name]

Adviser Name: [Insert Name]

Date of Meeting: [DD/MM/YYYY]

Transcript Reference: [File ID/Link]

2. Fact-Find / Know Your Customer (COBS 9.2.2R)

To be completed before any personal recommendation is made.

Financial Position

Annual Income: {{Extract gross/net income figures}}

Regular Expenditure: {{Extract committed and discretionary spending}}

Current Assets: {{Detail bank accounts, existing investments, property, etc.}}

Current Liabilities: {{Detail mortgages, loans, or other debts}}

Knowledge & Experience

Investment History: {{Detail types of products held currently or in the past}}

Financial Literacy: {{Summarise the client's understanding of financial markets and risks}}

3. Risk Tolerance Assessment (COBS 9.2.2R + FG11-05)

Assessing the client’s psychological willingness to take risk.

Risk Attitude: {{Describe the client’s self-described attitude toward market volatility}}

Risk Preferences: {{Note any specific constraints or preferences mentioned by the client}}

Discrepancy Check: {{Note if the client's stated risk profile conflicts with their actual experience}}

4. Capacity for Loss (COBS 9.2.2R(1)(b) + FG11-05)

Assessing the client’s objective ability to absorb falls in investment value.

Impact of Capital Loss: {{How would a 20% drop in value affect the client's standard of living?}}

Emergency Fund: {{Identify if a separate 3-6 month cash reserve exists}}

Financial Resources: {{Identify other assets that could be called upon in an emergency}}

5. Financial Objectives & Priorities (COBS 9.2.3R)

Specific goals, time horizons, and priorities.

Primary Investment Purpose: {{e.g., Retirement, school fees, capital growth}}

Time Horizon: {{Quantify the intended duration of the investment}}

Goal Prioritisation:
1. High: {{Primary objective}}
2. Medium: {{Secondary objective}}
3. Low: {{Tertiary objective}}
